The paper focuses on the design of user interfaces, which is a core topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of mixed integer linear programming (MILP) for generating grid-based layouts is a mathematical optimization technique, which falls under the category of computational geometry and graph theory (cs.GR). The paper also discusses techniques for interactive diversification, enhancement, and completion of grid layouts, which involve artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.SI) methods. Finally, the paper presents a wireframing tool that provides real-time layout suggestions, which is an application of computer engineering (cs.CE).
